            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "[Key idea](https://lobste.rs/s/prsi0f/rethinking_helix#c_f7biu0) of Helix select-action model: \n\n> The point of selecting before acting is that the commands can compose to a much greater degree. With helix, you can make a selection, perform an action on that selection (which *preserves the selection*), then expand the selection, perform two more actions, etc.\n\nOpen questions:\n\n- model visual-mode operation as a new \"operator\" ?\n- how do plugins like https://github.com/inkarkat/vim-visualrepeat and https://github.com/chrisbra/NrrwRgn re-apply a \"visual operation\"?\n\n",
